<br>
The old EQ with Brad was just fine.  Brad and co. had a direction and a purpose.  That drove EQ up into late Velious/Early Luclin.  After that, direction and purpose moved from content to some mathmatical equation that resulted in the most players paying monthly subscriptions for as long as possible.  And, ultimately, I'd rather see a game with purpose and vision that I might not necessarily agree with over a game that takes a poll to decide which direction is good for the month!<br>
<br>
Having said that, and to answer your question, City of Heroes is a blast for some lighter gameplay.  My gosh, you can spend hours on character creation and that is almost like a game in and of itself.  But beware, the game is pretty simple.  Depending on the choices you make during character selection, it varies from almost a FPS that is multiplayer to an obscure FPS that is multiplayer.  That is to say, character creation choices have a BIG impact on solo vs. grouping.  But overall, about any choice can solo.  And you won't see any big raid situations for quite awhile.<br>
<br>
Bottom line, CoH is a fun game to pop into when you got an hour or 3.  If you want something more, it's not there....yet.<br>
