<br>
As a new EQ player, it would have been more fun jumping into the world when no one knew anything about the game than it would be jumping into a world where some people have been playing it for years and you are just a n00b.<br>
<br>
That aside, I'd say game play is much better now than it was at release.  Think about all the changes..ya, no spell book...new UI, Spell sets etc.  For bards, remember when we didn't have a casting timer? Ya I could twist without it, but I still like having one.  How about the bard buff box?  Remember anyone, being in a group and having them tell you not to play songs because they didn't have the slots for it? On a raid?  As a game and as a class we are still better off than we were when the game launched.  <br>
